        <abstract> 
<p>Just finished HWB’s paper ["Contributions to an insect fauna of the Amazon valley", <hi rend="italic">Trans. Linn. Soc. Lond.</hi> 23 (1862): 495–566], one of the most remarkable he has ever read. Found mimetic cases and connection of facts marvellous. Finds equally important the facts on variation and segregation of complete and semi-complete species. Questions whether insect mimicry is not due to small size and defencelessness. Criticises title of paper. Mentions that Wallace will appreciate it.</p> 
        </abstract>
